title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: AACR Project GENIE publicly accessible international cancer registry real-world data assembled data sharing 19 leading cancer centers world. GENIE aggregates, harmonizes, links clinical-grade, next-generation cancer genomic sequencing data clinical outcomes obtained routine medical practice cancer patients treated institutions, although clinical information available limited (~<10 variables).

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: goal Project GENIE BPC (Biopharma Collaborative) augment existing registry genomic data enhanced clinical (phenomic) data support clinical-genomics analyses. Phenomic data curated using PRISSMM curation model. Currently MSK, Dana Farber, Vanderbilt University Health Network participating institutions. GENIE BPC expanded institutions phase II. GENIE BPC sponsors six projects involve augmenting genomic data Project GENIE include PRISSMM phenomic data cancer-related outcomes. project encompasses single cancer site. projects based curating data PRISSMM phenomic data curation model, variables available project may vary. six projects : Non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) Colon/rectal cancer (CRC) Breast cancer (BrCa) Pancreas cancer (PANC) Prostate cancer (Prostate) Bladder cancer (BLADDER)

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: GENIE BPC comprised several phenomic (clinical) elements include data AACR Project GENIE Tier 1 registry, institutions’ tumor registries, manual curation based institutions’ electronic health records (PRISSMM phenomic data model), derived variables based data elements. elements : Patient Characteristics Cancer Diagnosis: BPC Project Cancer Cancer Diagnosis: Non-BPC Project Cancer Cancer-Directed Drugs PRISSMM Imaging PRISSMM Pathology PRISSMM Medical Oncologist Assessments PRISSMM Tumor Marker Cancer Panel Test vignette describe structure element (dataset).

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: Patient Characteristics dataset structured one record per patient. dataset includes variables date death, last known alive date, number pathology reports, imaging reports, medical oncologist assessments, along many demographic vital status variables. Patient Characteristics dataset can linked datasets using record_id.

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: Two Cancer Diagnosis datasets provided: BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis dataset Non-BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis dataset.

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis dataset contains one record per BPC Project cancer diagnosis, per patient. BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis dataset can linked following datasets: Cancer-Directed Regimen dataset using variables record_id ca_seq Cancer Panel Test dataset using variables record_id ca_seq Patient Characteristics, PRISSMM Pathology, PRISSMM Imaging, PRISSMM Medical Oncologist Assessment datasets using record_id

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: Non-BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis dataset contains one record per non-BPC Project cancer diagnosis, per patient. dataset includes two types cancer diagnoses: 1) non-BPC Project invasive cancer situ/non-invasive cancer diagnoses, 2) tumors. Non-BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis dataset can linked following datasets: Cancer-Directed Regimen Dataset using variables record_id ca_seq Patient Characteristics, PRISSMM Pathology, PRISSMM Imaging, PRISSMM Medical Oncologist Assessment datasets using record_id linked Cancer Panel Test dataset non-BPC Project cancer diagnoses genomically sequenced

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: Cancer-Directed Regimen dataset structured one record per regimen-associated cancer diagnosis, per patient. Cancer-directed regimens curated cancer diagnoses, including BPC Project non-BPC Project cancers. regimen can consist one drug five drugs given together. Cancer-directed drugs include anti-neoplastic drugs, immunotherapies, targeted therapies, hormone therapies. break treatment ≥8 weeks used indicate end regimen; even drugs regimen re-initiated 8+ weeks later, considered new regimen. cancer-directed drug part investigational drug trial, drug name(s) drugs_drug_1-drugs_drug_5 set “Investigational Drug” end date interval match start date interval. Identification investigational drugs varies institution depending contractual obligations. institutions, drugs part investigational trial required masked, even standard care. institutions, investigational drug(s) required masked. Cancer-Directed Regimen can linked following datasets: BPC Project non-BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis datasets using variables record_id ca_seq Cancer Panel Test dataset using variables record_id ca_seq Patient Characteristics, PRISSMM Pathology, PRISSMM Imaging, PRISSMM Medical Oncologist Assessment datasets using record_id

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: Cancer-Directed Radiation Therapy dataset structured one record per radiation therapy-associated cancer diagnosis, per patient. example, radiation therapy associated single cancer diagnosis, one corresponding record dataset. radiation therapy associated two cancer diagnoses, two corresponding records dataset: one first associated cancer diagnosis another second associated cancer diagnosis. unknown cancer diagnosis radiation therapy associated , still one record dataset. Radiation therapy curated beginning within 30 days first BPC Project cancer diagnosis. subsequent radiation therapies recorded. Additional radiation therapy corresponding non-BPC Project Cancers may recorded. Radiation therapy data available following cohorts: PANC, Prostate, BLADDER. dataset can linked following datasets: BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis, Non-BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis, Cancer-Directed Regimen, Cancer Panel Test datasets datasets using variables cohort, record_id ca_seq Patient Characteristics, PRISSMM Pathology, PRISSMM Imaging, PRISSMM Medical Oncologist Assessment datasets using cohort record_id.

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: PRISSMM Pathology dataset structured one record per pathology report, per patient. pathology reports beginning month year first BPC Project cancer diagnosis subsequent pathology reports recorded (including pathology reports corresponding non-BPC Project cancer subsequent BPC Project cancer diagnoses). PRISSMM Pathology dataset can linked following datasets: Cancer Panel Test dataset using record_id, ca_seq, path_proc_number path_report_number Patient Characteristics, BPC Project Non-BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis, Cancer-Directed Regimen, PRISSMM Imaging, PRISSMM Medical Oncologist Assessment datasets using record_id

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: PRISSMM Imaging dataset structured one record per imaging report, per patient. imaging reports beginning month year first BPC Project cancer diagnosis subsequent imaging reports recorded (including imaging reports corresponding non-BPC Project cancer subsequent BPC Project cancer diagnoses). PRISSMM Imaging dataset can linked datasets using variable record_id.

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: PRISSMM Medical Oncologist Assessment dataset structured one row per curated medical oncologist assessment, per patient. Medical oncologist assessments curated beginning month year first BPC Project cancer diagnosis. One medical oncologist assessment per month curated. PRISSMM Medical Oncologist Assessment dataset can linked datasets using variable record_id.

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: PRISSMM Tumor Marker dataset structured one record per curated tumor marker result, per patient. serum-based tumor markers related diagnosis/prognosis cancer curated. Tumor marker data available following cohorts: CRC, BrCa, PANC, Prostate. Note: variables pertaining PD-L1, MSI MMR recorded pathology dataset. PRISSMM Tumor Marker dataset can linked datasets using variable record_id.

title: Tutorial: GENIE BPC Data Structure
text: Cancer Panel Test dataset structured one record per cancer panel test associated cancer diagnosis, per patient. cancer panel test refers multi-gene panels performed next generation sequencing (NGS) assays. terms “cancer panel test (CPT)” “next generation sequencing (NGS)” used interchangeably. Cancer Panel Test dataset can linked following datasets: BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis dataset using variables record_id ca_seq Cancer-Directed Regimen dataset using variables record_id ca_seq PRISSMM Pathology dataset using record_id, ca_seq, path_proc_number path_report_number Note: dataset linked non-BPC Project Cancer Diagnosis dataset non-BPC Project cancer diagnoses genomically sequenced.

title: Tutorial: create_analytic_cohort
text: create_analytic_cohort() function allows user create cohort GENIE BPC data based cancer diagnosis information cancer cohort, treating institution, histology, stage diagnosis, well cancer-directed regimen information including regimen name regimen order. function returns three datasets: cohort_ca_dx contains cancer diagnosis information patients matching specified criteria. dataset structured one record per patient per associated cancer diagnosis. cohort_ca_drugs returns drug-regimen information patients matching specified criteria. dataset structured one record per patient, per regimen associated cancer diagnosis. example, drug regimen associated treating two cancer diagnoses two records dataset. cohort_ngs contains next generation sequencing report information patients matching specified criteria. dataset structured one record per next generation sequencing report, per associated diagnosis. unknown cancer sequence associated next generation sequencing report, two records dataset. dataset contains key merge clinical genomic data. vignette walk user create_analytic_cohort() function.

title: Tutorial: create_analytic_cohort
text: create_analytic_cohort() function includes several input parameters: data_synapse index_ca_seq institution stage_dx histology regimen_drugs regimen_type regimen_order regimen_order_type return_summary function returns list data frames containing cancer diagnosis (cohort_ca_dx), cancer-directed regimen (cohort_ca_drugs) next generation sequencing (cohort_ngs) information patients met specified criteria. Optionally, return_summary = TRUE, list also includes summary tables number records per dataset (tbl_overall_summary) well tables key cancer diagnosis (tbl_cohort), cancer-directed regimen (tbl_drugs) next generation sequencing (tbl_ngs) variables.

title: create_analytic_cohort — create_analytic_cohort
text: data_synapse item nested list returned pull_data_synapse() corresponding cancer cohort interest. index_ca_seq Index cancer sequence. Default 1, indicating patient's first index cancer. index cancer also referred BPC Project cancer GENIE BPC Analytic Data Guide; cancer met eligibility criteria project selected random PRISSMM phenomic data curation. Specifying multiple index cancer sequences, e.g. index_ca_seq = c(1, 2) return index cancers patients 1 index cancer return first second index cancers patients multiple. institution GENIE BPC participating institution. Must one "DFCI", "MSK", "UHN", "VICC" NSCLC cohorts; must one "DFCI", "MSK", "VICC" CRC. Default selection institutions. parameter corresponds variable `institution` Analytic Data Guide. stage_dx Stage diagnosis. Must one "Stage ", "Stage II", "Stage III", "Stage -III NOS", "Stage IV". Default selection stages. parameter corresponds variable `stage_dx` Analytic Data Guide. histology Cancer histology. cancer cohorts except BrCa (breast cancer), parameter corresponds variable `ca_hist_adeno_squamous` must one "Adenocarcinoma", "Squamous cell", "Sarcoma", "Small cell carcinoma", "Carcinoma", "histologies/mixed tumor".  BrCa, parameter corresponds variable `ca_hist_brca` must one "Invasive lobular carcinoma", "Invasive ductal carcinoma", "histology". Default selection histologies. regimen_drugs Vector names drugs cancer-directed regimen, separated comma. example, specify regimen consisting Carboplatin Pemetrexed, specify regimen_drugs = "Carboplatin, Pemetrexed". Acceptable values found `drug_regimen_list` dataset provided package. parameter corresponds variable `regimen_drugs` Analytic Data Guide. regimen_type Indicates whether regimen(s) specified `regimen_drugs` indicates exact regimen return, regimens containing drugs listed `regimen_drugs` returned. Must one "Exact" "Containing". default "Exact". regimen_order Order cancer-directed regimen. multiple drugs specified, `regimen_order` indicates regimen order drugs; different values `regimen_order` specified different drug regimens. multiple values specified, e.g. c(1, 2), drug regimens met either order criteria returned. regimen_order_type Specifies whether `regimen_order` parameter refers order receipt drug regimen within cancer diagnosis (across drug regimens; "within cancer") order receipt drug regimen within times drug regimen administered (e.g. first time carboplatin pemetrexed received, times patient received carboplatin pemetrexed; "within regimen"). Acceptable values "within cancer" "within regimen". return_summary Specifies whether summary table cohort returned. Default FALSE. `gtsummary` package required return summary table.

title: create_analytic_cohort — create_analytic_cohort
text: list data frames containing cancer diagnosis (`cohort_ca_dx`), cancer-directed regimen (`cohort_ca_drugs`) next generation sequencing (`cohort_ngs`) information patients met specified criteria. Optionally, return_summary = TRUE, list also includes summary tables number records per dataset (`tbl_overall_summary`) well tables key cancer diagnosis (`tbl_cohort`), cancer-directed regimen (`tbl_drugs`) next generation sequencing (`tbl_ngs`) variables.

what: genieBPC: Data Processing Pipeline for the AACR Project GENIE Biopharma Collaborative Data — genieBPC-package
title: genieBPC: Data Processing Pipeline for the AACR Project GENIE Biopharma Collaborative Data — genieBPC-package
text: American Association Research Project Genomics Evidence Neoplasia Information Exchange (GENIE) BioPharma Collaborative represents multi-year, multi-institution effort build pan-cancer repository linked clinico-genomic data. genomic clinical data provided multiple releases (separate releases cancer cohort updates following data corrections), stored data sharing platform Synapse. genieBPC package provides seamless way obtain data corresponding release Synapse prepare datasets analysis.

what: Obtain Clinical Data Files for GENIE BPC Project — pull_data_synapse
title: Obtain Clinical Data Files for GENIE BPC Project — pull_data_synapse
text: `pull_data_synapse` function accesses specified  version clinical genomic GENIE BPC data  Synapse  reads R environment.   Documentation corresponding clinical data files   can also found Synapse Analytic Data Guide: NSCLC v1.1-Consortium Analytic Data Guide NSCLC v2.1-Consortium Analytic Data Guide NSCLC v2.0-Public Analytic Data Guide CRC v1.1-Consortium Analytic Data Guide CRC v1.2-Consortium Analytic Data Guide BrCa v1.1-Consortium Analytic Data Guide Users must log Synapse access data successfully. set Synapse credentials session, call: `set_synapse_credentials(username = "your_username", password = "your_password")` store authentication information environmental variables, add following .Renviron file (tip: can use usethis::edit_r_environ() easily open/edit file): `SYNAPSE_USERNAME = <-username>` `SYNAPSE_PASSWORD = <-password>` Alternatively, can pass username password individual data pull function preferred, although recommended manage passwords outside scripts security purposes.

title: Obtain Clinical Data Files for GENIE BPC Project — pull_data_synapse
code: pull_data_synapse(   cohort = NULL,   version = NULL,   download_location = NULL,   username = NULL,   password = NULL )

title: Obtain Clinical Data Files for GENIE BPC Project — pull_data_synapse
text: cohort Vector list specifying cohort(s) interest. Must one "NSCLC" (Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer),  "CRC" (Colorectal Cancer), "BrCa" (Breast Cancer). version Vector specifying version data. Must one following: "v1.1-consortium", "v1.2-consortium", "v2.1-consortium", "v2.0-public". entering multiple cohorts, order version numbers corresponds order cohorts specified; cohort version number must order order pull correct data. See examples . download_location `NULL` (default), data returned list dataframes requested data list items. Otherwise, specify folder path data automatically downloaded . path specified, data read R environment. username Synapse username password Synapse password

title: Obtain Clinical Data Files for GENIE BPC Project — pull_data_synapse
text: Returns nested list clinical genomic data corresponding specified cohort(s).

title: select_unique_ngs — select_unique_ngs
text: Get unique next generation sequencing sample patient analysis following several user define criterions.

title: select_unique_ngs — select_unique_ngs
code: select_unique_ngs(   data_cohort,   oncotree_code = NULL,   sample_type = NULL,   min_max_time = NULL )

title: select_unique_ngs — select_unique_ngs
text: data_cohort output object create_analytic_cohort function. oncotree_code character vector specifying sample OncoTree codes keep. See "cpt_oncotree_code" column data_cohort argument get options. sample_type character specifying type genomic sample prioritize, options "Primary", "Local" "Metastasis". Default select NGS sample based sample type. min_max_time character specifying first last genomic sample recorded kept. Options "min" (first) "max" (last).

title: select_unique_ngs — select_unique_ngs
text: returns 'cohort_ngs' object create_analytic_cohort unique genomic samples taken patients.

title: select_unique_ngs — select_unique_ngs
code: if(genieBPC:::.check_synapse_login() == TRUE){ #' # Example 1 ---------------------------------- # Create a cohort of all patients with stage # IV NSCLC of histology adenocarcinoma nsclc_2_0 <- pull_data_synapse("NSCLC", version = "v2.0-public") out <- create_analytic_cohort(data_synapse = nsclc_2_0$NSCLC_v2.0, stage_dx = c("Stage IV"), histology = "Adenocarcinoma") samples_data <- select_unique_ngs(data_cohort = out$cohort_ngs) # Example 2 ---------------------------------- # Create a cohort of all NSCLC patients who # received Cisplatin, Pemetrexed Disodium or Cisplatin, # Etoposide as their first drug regimen out <- create_analytic_cohort(data_synapse = nsclc_2_0$NSCLC_v2.0, regimen_drugs = c("Cisplatin, Pemetrexed Disodium", "Cisplatin, Etoposide"), regimen_order = 1, regimen_order_type = "within regimen") samples_data <- select_unique_ngs(data_cohort = out$cohort_ngs, oncotree_code = "LUAD", sample_type = "Metastasis", min_max_time = "max") } #> Error in dplyr::mutate(., file_info = map(.data$query_url, function(x) {    requestedObjects <- list(includeEntity = TRUE, includeAnnotations = TRUE,         includeFileHandles = TRUE, includeRestrictionInformation = TRUE)    res_per_id <- httr::POST(url = x, body = jsonlite::toJSON(requestedObjects,         pretty = T, auto_unbox = T), httr::add_headers(Authorization = paste("Bearer ",         token, sep = "")), httr::content_type("application/json"))    entityBundle <- httr::content(res_per_id, "parsed", encoding = "UTF-8")    file_info <- entityBundle$fileHandles[[1]]    bind_cols(type = file_info$contentType, name = file_info$fileName,         file_handle_id = file_info$id)})): Problem while computing `file_info = map(...)`. #> Caused by error in `entityBundle$fileHandles[[1]]`: #> ! subscript out of bounds
